Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp} for the noodles.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated). Cut the @lime{1/2} into wedges.

Trim the @green beans{80%g} and cut into thirds.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @egg noodle nests{2} and green beans.

Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and run under cold water to stop the noodles
sticking together and to keep the veg vibrant.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} to the pan and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.
> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken cooks, in a #jug{} or bowl, mix together the @water{150%ml}
and @sugar{1}(for the sauce), @soy sauce{15%ml}, @peanut butter{30%g} and
@ketjap manis{25%ml}.

> TIP: The peanut butter will loosen more when it warms up in the hot pan.

Once the chicken is cooked, add the @yellow Thai style paste{45%g} and garlic
to the pan. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the cooked noodles, beans and peanut sauce, stirring until well combined,
~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash to loosen the sauce if needed.

Add a generous squeeze of lime juice. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}
if needed.

Share your peanut noodles between your #bowls{}.

Serve with any remaining lime wedges alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!